com.yworks.yfiles.view.input

Class PopulateMenuEventArgs

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.view.input.InputModeEventArgs
      • com.yworks.yfiles.view.input.PopulateMenuEventArgs
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IEventArgs
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PopulateItemContextMenuEventArgs

    public class PopulateMenuEventArgs
extends InputModeEventArgs
    Event arguments for the PopulateMenu event.

    Event handlers can modify the Menu accordingly and set ShowingMenuRequested to true. Setting ShowingMenuRequested to false will cause the event to be marked as Handled and no menu will be shown.

      • isHandled

        public final boolean isHandled()
        Gets a value indicating whether this PopulateMenuEventArgs has been handled.

        This property is automatically set to true if ShowingMenuRequested has been assigned a value. Marking this event as handled tells the issuer of the query whether the ShowingMenuRequested property should be used or whether additional logic should be used to determine whether to show the menu.

        Returns:
        true if handled; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        setHandled(boolean)

      • isShowingMenuRequested

        public final boolean isShowingMenuRequested()
        Gets a value indicating whether to actually display the context menu.

        This will set the Handled property to true.

        Returns:
        true if the menu should be shown; false otherwise.
